<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Songri Ends Guo'an's Unbeaten Streak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou Songri's only goal in
the 13th round snapped the visiting Beijing Guo'an's unbeaten
streak of 12 games in the Chinese professional soccer league here
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Guo'an, ranked third in the 14-team league, came to their
13th game of the season with a record of five wins and seven draws
and remained the only unbeaten team as the 26-round season
reaching its mid-point.
</P>
<P>
The fifth ranked Songri came out with a solid defence and
forced the all-around attacking Guo'an into the goalless first
half.
</P>
<P>
The patient Songri finally grabbed they winning chance at the
54th minute when Zhao Changhong fired it home by following up a
reverse pass by Hu Zhijun just just in front of the goalmouth.
</P>
<P>
With one of their strikers Li Dongbo being sent out with his
second yellow card, the Guo'an had no means to pull back the game
and marked their first defeat of the seaon since last March.
</P>
<P>
League leaders Dalian Wanda was drawn by Shanghai Shenhua 1-1
after a 0-0 first half. Dalian remained on top of the 14-team
standings with eight wins, two losses and three ties, followed by
Shenhua in the second at 6-6-1.
</P>
<P>
In a fast attacking game played in Wuhan, the visiting Shandong
Luneng routed the hosts Yaqi 4-2 after leading the first 45-minute
by two unanswered goals.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang Haishi moved up from ninth to eighth after beating
Yanbian Aodong 1-0.
</P>
<P>
In other 13th round games, Chinese Army tied with Sichuan
Quanxing 0-0 and Shenzhen Ping'an was drawn 1-1 by Vanguards
Huandao. Qinghao Hainiu and Guanzhou Apollo each took one point
after another 0-0 game on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
