<HEADLINE> Cuba Edges Slovakia in Overtime for 7th Place </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Cuba prevented from the brink of a
defeat in the dying seconds to clinch an 83-81 overtime victory
over Slovakia on Sunday, taking seventh place at the Women's World
Basketball Championship.
</P>
<P>
The game was a repeat of the deciding playoff in the last
championship four yeas ago when Slovakia beat Cuba 92-81 to grab
fifth in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Cuba led the first half 45-42 but could never pull away and was
equalled 75-75 on Alena kovocova's inside basket at the buzz,
which forced the game into the overtime.
</P>
<P>
Though leading the score from the beginning of the extra five
minutes, the Cubains didn't feel comfortable until last few
seconds as Taimara Coronado hit one free throw for the final
scores.
</P>
<P>
Grisel Herrera Mendez led Cuba with 25 points, including eight
three-pointers while Juditc Aguila Hernandez added 17.
</P>
<P>
Anna Kotocova scored 19 points to top the Slovakians and Zuzana
Kamenikova was 14-point scorer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
