<HEADLINE> African States Called on to Contribute to OAU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) has called on its member states in position to make
voluntary contributions to the OAU peace fund following those
made by seven African countries.
</P>
<P>
The fund, set up in March 1993, is to draw resources to
finance various operations and seminars on peace mission across
the continent.
</P>
<P>
Up to the end of March this year, the total contribution to
the fund, including materials, stood at 25.92 million
U.S.Dollars, with 17.63 million from outside Africa, according to
Salim Ahmed Salim, the OAU Secretary-General.
</P>
<P>
In his report to the current 68th ordinary session of the OAU
Council of Ministers, Salim disclosed that 19.94 million Dollars
out of the total had been expended up to March 31 this year.
</P>
<P>
Some 13.92 million Dollars were spent on preventive diplomacy
activities including peace operations in Burundi.
</P>
<P>
A resolution of the council of ministers meeting to end here
Sunday night, urged the memberstates to increase the share of
the African contribution to facilitate peace operations in the
continent.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also decided to increase the proportion of the
annual contribution to the peace fund by member states from the
five percent to six percent of the oau regular budget.
</P>
<P>
The increase of the fund is expected to help strengthen the
OAU Mechanism for Conflict Prevention, Management and Resolution.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
