<HEADLINE> Spain Takes Fifth Place at Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Spain defeated Lithuania 70-59 with
spurt in the last minutes here on Sunday, stepping up to fifth
place of the 13th Women's World Basketball Championship.
</P>
<P>
Guard Belen Alvaro hit 18 points to lead the Spanish team, who
was the eighth place finisher four years ago in Sydney, and center
Pilar Valero contributed 17. Forward Aamaya Valdemoro, who led
Spain with 27 points on Saturday's game against Cuba, added 10 and
grabbed 11 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
Forward Jolanta Vilutyte was Lithuania's top scorer with 14
points, followed by Dal Kurtinaitiene's 12 and Lin Dambrauskaite's
10.
</P>
<P>
European champion Lithuania, who made their debut at the world
champpionship, took a 36-35 narrow lead in the first half.
However, Spain took it over less than two minutes later and pulled
away after a 53-53 tie in the second.
</P>
<P>
In the classification deciding seventh to eighth earlier
Sunday, Cuba edged Slovakia 83-81 to take seventh.
</P>
<P>
Later on Sunday, defending champion Brazil will play against
Australia for the bronze medal while the United States meets
Russia in the gold medal final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
