<HEADLINE> Enid Blyton Announces Asia Joint Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Enid Blyton Sunday announced the
formation of a substantial new joint venture company, Enid Blyton
(Asia) Pte Limited.
</P>
<P>
The new company will give Enid Blyton a significant presence in
the vast Asian market and will enable the company to greatly
increase its opportunities for extending business in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The Enid Blyton, a recipient of the Queen's Award for Export,
focuses on developing broadcast, publishing, licensing and
merchandising activity.
</P>
<P>
Enid Blyton (Asia) Pte Limited will operate from Hong Kong and
cover all countries in the Asian region including Australia, New
Zealand, India, Japan, South Korea, the Philippines and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture company will have the same rights as the Enid
Blyton Company enabling it to build close, long lasting and
mutually beneficial partnerships with Asian companies and
individuals who are recognized experts in their own specialist
fields.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the launching of the joint venture, David Lane,
managing director of the Enid Blyton Company, said, "While we have
had a presence in Asia for a number of years, we believe that it
is culturally and economically difficult to maximize the real
potential of Enid Blyton in Asia from a UK base."
</P>
<P>
"Our joint venture partners will bring local knowledge,
experience and the specific market expertise to enable Enid Blyton
(Asia) Pte Limited to penetrate these important and diverse
markets," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
