<HEADLINE> China Wins Malaysia Open Table Tennis Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 7 (Xinhua) -- China bagged all titles at
stake in the four-day Malaysian Open Table Tennis championships
held in Kota Kinabalu, East Malaysia's Sabah State, which closed
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Ma lin defeated his campatriot topseed Kong Linghui in the
final Sunday to win the men's singles title, according to reports
reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year old Ma Lin, in search of his first title, put up a
gallant show with unrelenting smashes before pulling off a major
upset over the former world champion 21-16, 20-22, 21-15, 18-21,
21-19.
</P>
<P>
Ma Lin, who had earlier shown Olympic gold medallist Liu
Guoliang, also from China, the exit in the semifinals, received
9,000 U.S. dollars and trophy.
</P>
<P>
Kong, partnering with Liu, however, retained the men's doubles
title after defeating China's pair of Wang Liqin and Yang Sen
18-21, 21-17, 21-11.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Ying emerged as the women's single champion after winning
an all-Chinese final agaisnt Wang Hui in 21-15, 24-22, 21-15.
</P>
<P>
Zhang received 6,000 U.S. dollars as the new champion.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Zhang and Wang Chen took the women's doubles title,
winning 10-21, 21-19, 21-9 over another Chinese pair Wang Hui and
Chang Hongxia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
