<HEADLINE> Pantani Wins Tour of Italy Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Marco Pantani of Italy won the Tour of
Italy ended in Milan on Sunday when the result of the 22nd and
final stage was cancelled due to heavy rain.
</P>
<P>
Pantani, 28, hold the lead into the final day and came out
ahead of Pavel Tonkov of Russia, who won two years ago, and
Giuseppe Guerini of Italy
</P>
<P>
Pantani, the best climber in the race, took the lead on Tuesday
at the end of a gruelling stage in the Dolomite mountains. He won
two stages, both in the mountains, at Piancavallo and
Montecampione. 
