<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAU Sees Positive Developments in Burundi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The developments within
Burundi, particularly the on-going national debate and the
establishment of partnership for peace between the government and
parliament, seem to have brought a flush of fresh air to African
leaders despite their many concerns.
</P>
<P>
At a ministerial meeting of the Organization of African Unity
(OAU) which is ending Sunday night, the participants expressed
hope that the developments will contribute to the relaunching of
the Arusha peace process and to laying the basis for genuine
national reconciliation in that country.
</P>
<P>
A resolution adopted by the 68th ordinary session of the OAU
council of ministers hailed the initiatives taken by Julius
Nyerere as facilitator to convene the inter-Burundian talks in
Arusha later this month.
</P>
<P>
All the parties concerned in Burundi are urged to take part in
and to endeavor to ensure the success of the talks aimed at
ending the country's political crisis.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the food crisis caused by prolonged drought, the
resolution appealed OAU member states and the international
community as a whole to lend humanitarian assistance to the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
