<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stock Exchange Index up 10 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait Stock Exchange index
went up by 10 points Sunday, closing at 2,173.5 points compared
with 2,163.5 points at Saturday's close.
</P>
<P>
However, the volume, transactions and value showed a mixed
result compared with those of Saturday with a total of 20.74
million shares over 729 deals. Saturday's trade volume was 23.71
million shares with 695 deals done.
</P>
<P>
The value of shares traded Sunday dropped to 5.30 million
Kuwaiti dinars (17.49 million U.S. dollars) from 7.20 million
dinars (23.76 million dollars) of the previous day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
