<HEADLINE> Zambian Minister Calls for Poor People's Easy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Health Minister Nkandu Luo
Sunday called for concerted efforts from all stakeholders to
ensure that all Zambian, especially the poor, have access to
medicines when they need them.
</P>
<P>
At the launching of the pharmacy awareness week here, Luo said
that although the majority of the Zambians still live in abject
poverty, the government is committed to ensureing that even the
poorest are able to get their medicines at affordable prices,
reported the Zambia News Agency.
</P>
<P>
"The govenment has introduced the national health reforms
which will ensure that even the poorest of the poor will get
their medicines whereever they are in zambia when they need
them," he said.
</P>
<P>
The minister also challenged the pharmacautical society of
Zambia to critically consider the establishment of pharmacautical
outlets in remote areas of the country.
</P>
<P>
Luo urged the society to contribute to the elinination of
street vending of medicines.
</P>
<P>
She added that the government will provide an appropriate
environment for the pharmacutical profession to thrive while
safeguarding the interests of the public.
</P>
<P>
And the government will also ensure that drugs and medical
supplies are procured in the most economical and cost effective
manner, said the minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
