<HEADLINE> African Ministers Call for Contribution to Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- African countries have
appealed to the international community to contribute to a
special continental fund for drought and famine in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The special emergency assistance fund for drought and famine
in Africa, set up by the Organization of African Unity (OAU), has
so far raised a total reserve of 5.75 million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
But more resources should be pooled for the fight against
Africa's continuous drought, famine and natural disasters, which
constitute a constant threat to the economy and the survival of
people in many African countries, according to OAU
Secretary-General Salim Ahmed Salim.
</P>
<P>
"The worsening food situation, the persistent drought in
Africa and insufficient and inadequate financial transfers have
made it imperative for us to translate into concrete action
African cooperation and solidarity," Salim told an OAU council of
ministers meeting.
</P>
<P>
The council of ministers, which will soon conclude its 68th
ordinary session here Sunday night, adopted a resolution,
extending an appeal for international aid to the fund.
</P>
<P>
The resolution "appeals to the international community,
governments, governmental and non-governmental organizations,
businessmen, as well as economic operators to contribute
generously to the fund," the resolution said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
