<HEADLINE> Air France Striking Pilots Vow to Continue Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The head of the principal union of
striking pilots of Air France said Sunday that the pilots are
determined to continue the strike until the end.
</P>
<P>
"We will go until the end of the conflict. The ball is in the
camp of the management of Air France," said Jean-Charles Corbet,
the president of the SNPL, the biggest pilots' union in France,
</P>
<P>
Air France pilots have been on strike since last Monday despite
the call by the government for a resumption of flights as the
football World Cup finals are nearing.
</P>
<P>
"The conflict will continue. But we hope to resume talks with
the management as soon as possible. I think they would resume," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The pilots are disputing a plan by the management to lower
their salaries by 15 percent in exchange for the company's shares.
</P>
<P>
They are also demanding the scrapping of a double standard in
pays for younger pilots, which are much lower than that for older
pilots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
