<HEADLINE> Chirac Says Security Essential Concern in World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac said
Sunday that security is the essential concern for France in the
upcoming football World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Agence France-Presse (AFP), Chirac also
called on the striking Air France pilots to end their week-long
strike and take up their responsibility.
</P>
<P>
"As for security, it is our essential concern. I know by
experience that, in this field, we can never be sure about
anything," he said.
</P>
<P>
But he said that France is doing all it can to ensure security
for all during the World Cup finals from June 10 to July 12.
</P>
<P>
"Concerning the strike or the demonstrations, each one should
evidently prove a spirit of responsibility. There will be credit
to the image of France," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also defended the stand of the French Committee of
Organization (CFO) in ticket distribution, saying that the CFO is
following the rule of the International Federation of Football
(FIFA).
</P>
<P>
The European Commission has severely criticized the CFO for its
way of distributing tickets, accusing it of being unfair to other
European countries.
</P>
<P>
"The ticket distribution concerns only the CFO and the FIFA. It
should be between the two that the problem be solved. To my
knowledge, the CFO has applied the rules of the FIFA," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that any abuse of drugs must be fought with
firmness during the matches.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the opening ceremony Wednesday, Chirac will also
attend the match between France and Denmark to be held in Lyon.
</P>
</TEXT>
