<HEADLINE> Air France Pilots Propose to Transport World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The striking pilots of Air France
proposed Sunday that the air company transport free football
World Cup ticket-holders despite the on-going strike by the
pilots.
</P>
<P>
Christian Paris, the spokesman of the pilots' union SNPL, said
on television that the pilots will propose creating special free
flights for ticket-holders.
</P>
<P>
"These planes will be piloted by striking pilots of our union
and free of pay. I think that Air France will at least give
preferential treatment, such as lower fare prices," he said.
</P>
<P>
Air France's communications department immediately responded
by calling the proposal "a positive gesture."
</P>
<P>
"The management will immediately get in touch with SNPL on the
question of transport during the World Cup, which could be solved
within 48 hours," said Air France communication director Francois
Brousse. 
</P>
