<HEADLINE> German Military Plane Evacuates 212 Europeans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A passenger plane of the German Air
Force has evacuated 212 European nationals from Eritrea and landed
late Sunday afternoon in the airport of the western German city of
Cologne.
</P>
<P>
Passengers on board the Airbus A-310 consisted of 94 Germans
and 118 nationals of other European countries, German officials
said.
</P>
<P>
It is said to be the first passenger plane that has flown in
the Asmara airport of Eritrea which had been bombed recently by
Ethiopia following a serious escalation in a border dispute
between the two African countries.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,500 foreigners had been evacuated from Eritrea by
German, U.S., British and Italian planes Saturday evening, German
news reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
