<HEADLINE> Iran Concerned Over Ethiopia-Eritrea Military </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Sunday expressed serious
concern over recent military clashes between Ethiopia and
Eritrea, calling on the two African countries to solve their
disputes through political means.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi said that
it is incorrect to solve differences and disputes by resorting to
force and hostility, Tehran radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi said that both Ethiopia and Eritrea should make use
of their natural resources and economic potentials for their
development, adding that Iran supports any sincere efforts to put
an end to the conflicts and bring tranquillity and stability to
the region.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia and Eritrea entered into a military confrontation
since Friday when they bombarded each other, but both sides
claimed that their actions were merely defensive.
</P>
<P>
The two African countries were one until Eritrea gained
independence in 1993. They are at odds over a border area that is
claimed by both sides. Both countries have used aircraft, tanks and
artillery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
