<HEADLINE> Africa Moves to Boost Economic Integration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- African ministers have decided
to invite their heads of state and government to be here for a
summit next monday to focus on the promotion of economic
integration in the continent.
</P>
<P>
At a ministerial meeting called by the Organization of African
Unity (OAU) which is to end Sunday night, the participants
discussed a report on the African Economic Community (AEC).
</P>
<P>
The report, made at the AEC Economic and Social Commission
meeting two months ago, covers a wide range of issues concerning
the structure and future operations of AEC, inaugarated at last
year's OAU summit in Harare, Zimbabwe, for continental economic
integration.
</P>
<P>
The issues include preparation for an AEC budget, cooperation
between AEC and other regional and sub-regional economic
communities, as well as the development strategies of the
community.
</P>
<P>
At the 68th ordinary session of the OAU council of ministers,
the ministers decided to submit the said report to the assembly
of heads of state and government for approval.
</P>
<P>
the meeting also called for scrupulous implementation of the
protocol on the relations between AEC and regional communities,
which was signed in February this year.
</P>
<P>
Regional economic communities which have not yet signed the
protocol are urged to do so as early as possible, while member
states of the Arab Magreb Union and those of AEC are also
requested to pursue efforts for normalizing relations.
</P>
<P>
For a continent that has been mired in almost two decades of
economic crisis, Africa has achieved encouraging economic growth
over the last few years.
</P>
<P>
To further promote the momentum, African countries are fully
aware that economic integration is the only way for collective
development.
</P>
<P>
Perfect performance of AEC is regarded as the first and most
important step to this end.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
