<HEADLINE> Cigarette Smugglings in Vietnam Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Cigarette smugglings in Vietnam are
increasing alarmingly, especially since late last year, the
Vietnam News Monday quoted the Trade Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, around 160 million packages of
cigarettes have been seized each year, according to an official of
the Trade ministry.
</P>
<P>
However, the official said the figure represented only about 10
percent of the cigarettes illegally brought into Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
From early December in 1997 to the end of February in 1998,
more than 6.2 million packages of cigarettes were confiscated.
</P>
<P>
High profit was the main reason of continued cigarette
smuggling. Because of the financial crisis in the Southeast
region, cigarette prices have become very cheap in the Southeast
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
