<HEADLINE> Hospitals Vow to Station Medical Teams in Poor Areas of Qinghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Up to 14 hospitals of Xining City,
capital of northwest China's Qinghai Province, have vowed to
station medical teams in 14 poor counties where local people are
living under the state-set poverty line.
</P>
<P>
A senior official with the provincial health department said
that the move aims to alleviate the lingering problems of local
people who have difficulty finding medical treatment when ill.
</P>
<P>
All 14 counties are located in mountainous areas and inhabited
by a variety of ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the provincial health department has
dispatched several medical teams to these areas, a move which has
met with unexpected success and warm welcome from local people.
</P>
<P>
Because of its success, the department has decided to institute
the program as a system, instead of occasionally dispatching
medical teams.
</P>
<P>
The department also has persuaded 14 hospitals to sign
contracts with the 14 counties, all pledging to station their
teams in the counties for at least six months each year.
</P>
<P>
Since early this year, the 14 hospitals have dispatched 104
medical teams to these counties, providing medical treatment for
100,000 local people.
</P>
<P>
Those hospitals have also donated some 2,300 pieces of medical
equipment to the 14 counties and trained more than 1,700 medical
workers for those areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
