<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President-Elect Joseph
Estrada said Monday that he expects his economic program to face
rough sailing due to the 8 billion pesos (204.6 million U.S.
dollars) budget deficit the Ramos administration will be leaving
behind.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, outgoing Budget Secretary Emilia Boncodin was reported
as saying that the huge budget deficit is already a "distinct
possibility" because "revenues (are) further deteriorating and the
avenue for further expenditure cuts (is) now practically closed."
</P>
<P>
