Estrada told reporters.
</P>
<P>
But Estrada expressed confidence that the economy will soon
recover, saying it has to face difficulties during the first few
months of his administration due to the deficit the Ramos
administration will be leaving behind.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said his administration will also examine the manner of
disposition of funds by the Ramos government, to determine whether
the public's money was wasted.
</P>
<P>
The Ramos government had earlier set a 5 billion peso surplus
target for the whole 1998, but decided to revise the figure to
just 1 billion pesos (25.6 million dollars). 
