<HEADLINE> Sino-German Joint Venture on Port Machinery Goes into Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A large-scale Sino-German joint
venture to make port-related machinery has gone into production
today in Longhai, a city in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The cooperative project was signed in November of 1996 when
German Chancellor Helmut Kohl visited China. And it was undertaken
by the China Merchants Company of Hong Kong and the Preussag Noell
Company of Germany.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture of Preussag Noell China Merchants Mechanical
Engineering Co. Ltd. involves an investment of 72 million German
marks, with the German company funding 70 percent of the
investment.
</P>
<P>
The venture mainly makes loading and unloading equipment and
various types of container cranes. And more than 70 percent of its
products will be exported.
</P>
<P>
The 170-year-old Preussag Noell firm, one of four major
manufacturing companies in Germany, has set up more than 200
subsidiary companies worldwide.  
</P>
