<HEADLINE> Auriol Takes Lead in Acropolis Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Frenchman Didier Auriol led the
Acropolis Rally after the second day Monday edging ahead of
Scotland's Colin McRae in a Subaru after a tough stage which ended
in Delphi.
</P>
<P>
Auriol, the 1994 world rally champion, burst ahead on the third
of the five specials and held on to end the day 4.8 seconds ahead
of the Scotsman who won the world title in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Finland's Juha Kankkunen, the four-times world champion, drove
his Ford Escort into third place overall, 13.3 seconds behind
Auriol.
</P>
<P>
World championship leader Carlos Sainz of Spain in a Toyota was
lying fourth 15.9 seconds adrift of the Frenchman
</P>
<P>
The rally finishes on the the third day Tuesday with a 328.73
kilometer stage which includes 128.29 kms in specials. The
Acropolis Rally is the eighth leg in the World Rally Championship.
