<HEADLINE> HK, Macao to Step Up Legal, Judicial Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Macao and the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) agreed on Monday to step up
cooperation in the legal and judiciary fields.
</P>
<P>
The two sides reached the consensus following a half-day
working visit to Macao by Elsie Leung Oi-Sie, secretary for
justice of the Hong Kong SAR. She came here at the invitation of
her Macao counterpart, Jorge Silveira.
</P>
<P>
During her visit, Leung briefed her host on the experience
gained in the legal and judicial fields since the establishment of
the Hong Kong SAR. The two sides also discussed the respective
legal systems in the two places and other legal and judicial
issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Leung said the two sides agreed to increase contacts in the
future. They also agreed that it is necessary for the two sides to
reach some agreements on mutual legal assistance, such as the
transfer of documents and the repatriation of criminals and
fugitive offenders.
</P>
<P>
Leung is the highest SAR official to visit Macao since the
founding of the Hong Kong SAR last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
