<HEADLINE> Chinese, Uruguayan Vice-Presidents Hold Talks in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao,
during a talk with his Uruguayan counterpart Hugo Batalla here
today, said that China is ready to work with Uruguay to advance a
long-term, stable and cooperative Sino-Uruguayan relationship
oriented toward the next century.
</P>
<P>
Sino-Uruguayan relations have registered a smooth development
featured with frequent exchange of high-level visits and effective
cooperation since the two nations forged diplomatic ties 10 years
ago, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
Hu voiced his appreciation of the "one China" policy pursued by
the Uruguayan government and his thanks to Uruguay's support of
China's access to the World Trade Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
He told Batalla that China is willing to cooperate with Uruguay
in various forms and channels to further enhance bilateral
economic and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Batalla said he totally agrees with Hu's evaluation on
the Uraguay-China relations.
</P>
<P>
The Uruguayan side hopes to further boost Uraguay-China economic
and technological collaboration with the process of China's access
into the WTO, Batalla said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that China would expand its investment in
Uraguay and said Uruguay is willing to play a positive role in
promoting the relations between China and the Common Market in
south Latin America.
</P>
<P>
The two vice-presidents also briefed each other on their
respective domestic situation and reached extensive consensus on
major international issues.
</P>
<P>
Hu expressed his admiration to the prolonged stable political
situation and the constant economic growth in Uruguay as well as
the country's important role in regional and world affairs.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Hu presided over a welcoming ceremony in
honor of Batalla, who is on an official visit to China as Hu's
guest. 
</P>
