global temperature records in each of the first five months of
1998, according to analysis by U.S. government scientists.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- Business activity in Pakistan is slowing due to
uncertainty about the impact of international sanctions
resulting from the country's nuclear tests.
</P>
<P>
-- A major ocean-shipping cartel will increase rates 15 percent
on shipments from the U.S. to Asia, the biggest boost since the
mid-1980s, which will affect shipping of American goods. The move
comes at a bad time for U.S. exporters, already battered by Asia's
economic woes because consumers there are buying fewer American
goods. 
</P>
