General Hagglund thanked the Chinese government for a rich and
well-arranged schedule, which has enabled him to visit different
armed services and military academies and schools.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of the foreign policy China has been pursuing
and appreciated the correct approaches it has adopted toward the
Asian financial crisis and the arms race in south Asia.
</P>
<P>
China is an important force in maintaining peace and stability
of Asia and in the world as a whole, Hagglund said.
</P>
<P>
Lieutenant General Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of the General
Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army, was among those
present at the meeting.  
