Jerusalem must be stopped and such activities could only cause
further damage to the peace process, Husseini said.
</P>
<P>
But the Jewish settlers said they had documents to prove that
their occupation of the houses were legal.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat's Information Advisor, Nabil
Abu Rodeineh, also voiced his strong indignation Monday at the
Jewish settlers' constant attempt to occupy the Palestinian houses
in the Old City, according to Jerusalem Media and Communication
Center.
</P>
<P>
The incident Monday dealt another blow to the long stalled
peace process, he said, adding that the occupation must come to an
end.
