<HEADLINE> Airmail Center Opens at New HK Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A Hongkong Post airmail center
opened at the new Hong Kong airport here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Situated at the airport in Chek Lap Kok, the
566-million-HK-dollar (72.6 million U.S. dollar) airmail center is
equipped with state-of-the-art mail handling technology capable of
handling the rapidly growing airmail traffic into the next
millennium, said Robert Footman, postmaster general of Hong Kong,
at the inaugural ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The new center will be fully operational on July 6, operating
24 hours, three shifts a day throughout the year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the inaugural ceremony, Financial Secretary Donald
Tsang said efficient, reliable and cost-effective postal services
are important in maintaining Hong Kong as a leading business
center in the world.
</P>
<P>
Tsang cited Hongkong Post as "one of the many good examples
which kept on improving services to customers, with a view to
strengthening Hong Kong's ability to compete in the world market."
</P>
<P>
According to Tsang, 90 percent of the mail Hongkong Post
handles comes from the business sector.
</P>
<P>
"The new center will bring our postal services into a new era,"
he noted.  
</P>
