<HEADLINE> China to Hold International Exhibition for Printing Techniques </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The Second China International
Exhibition of Printing Equipment and Appliances will be held in
Beijing on June 9-13. More than 200 companies from both at home and
abroad will attend.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will display the world's most advanced printing
equipment, testing appliances and instruments in an exhibition
area of 8,000 square meters. The companies from dozens of nations
-- including Belgium, Germany, Italy, France, the United States,
Japan, India and Switzerland -- will introduce their latest
breakthroughs in such printing technologies as digital processing
systems and multimedia.
</P>
<P>
China has made progress in its printing industry with offset
lithography, digital printing and computer-aided composition
technologies widely used in printing houses at all levels,
industry officials said.
</P>
<P>
However, the country still has a huge untapped market
potential. According to 1996 statistics, the Chinese each bought
only six books, two magazines and 22 newspapers annually, which
leaves room for future growth.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is being jointly sponsored by China Printing
Materials Company and China International Exhibition Center.
