<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-08 12:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tehran Mayor Likely to Be Convicted: Moderates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Following Sunday's first session of
the trial of Tehran Mayor Gholamhussein Karbaschi, Iran's
moderates held the view that he is likely be convicted by the
court.
</P>
<P>
A report on the daily Iran News said on Monday that Iranian
Vice President Abdolvahed Mousavi Lari and several moderate Majlis
(Parliament) members believed that Karbaschi, a moderate
technocrat, would be found guilty but the report did not give
reasons.
</P>
<P>
The conservative bloc has so far kept silent about the court
proceedings against the close ally of President Mahammad Khatami,
who was charged with embezzlement, misappropriation of public
funds and mismanagement.
</P>
<P>
Khatami came to power after defeating his hardline competitor
by a landslide in the presidential election in May last
year. Karbaschi is believed to have contributed to his success by,
for one thing, helping financing his campaign.
</P>
<P>
At the court, Karbaschi rejected as "baseless" all the
corruption charges brought against him, but his self-defense was
frequently disrupted by the judge, who dismissed his allegation
that there was any prejudice against him.
</P>
<P>
The next session of the trial is scheduled for Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The case has become a hot topic in the country and caused tense
political struggle between the conservatives and moderates.
</P>
<P>
On April 4, Karbaschi was detained by the conservative
judiciary and stayed in jail for 11 days before the intervention
by the supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, who wanted to keep
factional struggle under control, led to his release.
</P>
<P>
The conservatives have since vowed to remove Karbaschi's
mayorship and even demanded an impeachment of his patron, Interior
Minister Abdullah Nouri. By regulations, mayor of Tehran is
usually chosen by interior minister and then confirmed by the
supreme leader.
</P>
<P>
Lari, the vice president, confirmed that Karbaschi's mayorship
has been suspended for the trial and one of his deputies is now
taking charge. But he said that no decision has been made on the
future of his position.
</P>
<P>
The conservatives also criticized the interior minister for
issuing permits to pro-Khatami gatherings in recent month, in one
case of 20 people were injured as clashes between supporters of
the rival factions broke out.
</P>
<P>
It is predicted here that Nouri will face a no-confidence vote
in the Majlis, now dominated by the conservatives.
</P>
<P>
Observers here believe that factional struggle has entered a
critical stage as the two sides are openly trading accusations and
some conservatives are pointing their finger direct at the
moderate president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
