<HEADLINE> Mozambique Confiscates 295 Bags of Marijuana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican police have detained two
people with 295 bags of marijuana (250 grams each bag) in Maputo,
police spokesman Abiliko Quive said here.
</P>
<P>
Quive said that the two people were caught Sunday at a bus
station, and they admitted that the marijuana has come from
northwestern Mozambique's Tete Province.
</P>
<P>
The suspected drug smugglers said that they has been carrying
drugs from Tete to Maputo since 1996.
</P>
<P>
Quive said 362 bags of marijuana, or 90 kgs, have been
confiscated since the police started their "Colombia Operation"
drive against drug smuggling and consumption in the country,
adding that more drug could be found.
</P>
<P>
The police spokesman also urged all walks of life to cooperate
and back the police in their operation against the drug.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that over 220 tons of drug have been transited
via Mozambique to the markets elsewhere in the past four years.
</P>
</TEXT>
