<HEADLINE> S. African Soccer Team Arrives in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 8 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's national soccer
team, Bafana Bafana, arrived in Vichy, France on Sunday for the
World Cup finals, South African media reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
About 2,000 wellwishers waited patiently from 2 p.m. (1300 GMT)
until the team bus rolled in at 7.30 p.m. (1830 GMT), The Star
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
"It's quite fantastic, what a way to start our final leg of
preparation for the World Cup finals," Bafana assistant coach
Trott Moloto was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The South Africans will be based there throughout the World Cup.
</P>
<P>
Coach Philippe Troussier arrived later, after accompanying
midfielder Brendan Augustine to a specialist who examined his
injured groin.
</P>
<P>
Troussier will announce Monday whether Augustine will be fit to
play or will return home be replaced by one of the three standby
players.
</P>
<P>
There was also a slight worry about the ankle injury sustained
by captain Lucas Radebe in the 1-1 draw against Iceland in
Bafana's final warmup friendly on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Bafana will play France Friday in Marseilles. 
</P>
