<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PBOC Steps Up Punishment on Malpractice in Financial Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC)
today issued its newly-drafted stipulations about the
administrative punishment on those who are responsible for
financial institutions' malpractice.
</P>
<P>
The Stipulations listed in detail various kinds of malpractice
that will face severe punishment, including financial
institutions' off-the-book operations; financial institutions'
depositing or loan-extending practices that run counter to
interest rate policies and related management regulations;
insurance companies lower charge rate or raise service fee
standard without authorization, as well as some other financial
practices which are not allowed by the law or related regulations.
</P>
<P>
The PBOC will measure the nature and responsibility of these
malpractice and accordingly make different administrative
punishment on those who are responsible.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the PBOC said that when a financial
institution's malpractice leads to capital losses or serious
consequences, its leaders will be seriously punished; when a
financial institution and its staff violate the law in their
operations, they will be referred to judicial departments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
