<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councillor Meets Former US President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Wu Yi told Former
US President Gorge Bush here today that China is making active
preparations for President Bill Clinton's upcoming China visit.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Wu said China hopes that President
Clinton's visit to China will be as successful as President Jiang
Zemin's US trip last year.
</P>
<P>
She noted that the exchange of high-level visits between two
countries will help further enhance bilateral ties and increase
the understanding of the people of both nations.
</P>
<P>
The forging of Sino-US constructive strategical partnership
oriented toward the 21st century is not only in the interests of
the two peoples, but also beneficial to peace and stability in the
world, she added.
</P>
<P>
Wu went on to say that the two countries should solve some
problems in the bilateral trade as early as possible so as to
further promote the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
George Bush said that most people in the United States have
become aware of the importance of bilateral ties and support
Clinton's China tour, although some people attempt to create some
obstacles for the growth of US-Chinese relations.
</P>
<P>
George Bush and his party are here as guests of the Chinese
People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries.
</P>
