<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Issue 45 Billion Yuan in Treasury Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Finance
announced today that the ministry plans to issue 45 billion yuan
in voucher treasury bonds from June 10 to October 31.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the ministry said the new bonds are part of the
bond-issuing schedule for this year. It aims to raise more funds
for economic construction and to meet residents' demand for buying
treasury bonds.
</P>
<P>
Of the total bonds to be issued, 27 billion yuan will be in
three-year bonds with an annual coupon rate of 7.11 percent, 18
billion yuan in five-year bonds with an annual interest rate of
7.86 percent, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The bonds cannot be listed or traded at the stock market,
neither can it be used for mortgage credit.
</P>
<P>
Individual investors can buy the bonds from the Industrial and
Commercial Bank, the Agricultural Bank of China, the China
Construction Bank, the Bank of China, the Bank of Communications,
as well as some other commercial banks and city cooperative banks,
the spokesman said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
