<HEADLINE> Ethiopia-Eritrea Conflict Tops OAU Summit Agenda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OUAGADOUGOU, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The escalating conflict
between Ethiopia and Eritrea is surely on top of the agenda of
the 34th Assembly of Heads of State and Government of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) which was just declared open
here Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The conflict between the two countries has shocked Africa,
and we will do our best to find a way to solve the conflict
during the meeting," said President of Burkina Faso Blaise
Compaore while addressing the 34th OAU summit which was declared
open by Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe, Chairman of the OAU.
</P>
<P>
Compaore will be the new Chairman of the OAU at the current
34th OAU summit to replace out-going Chairman Mugabe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
