<HEADLINE> Macao to Issue Stamps to Mark World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Macao will issue a set of new stamps
to mark the upcoming '98 World Cup when it begins on June 10 in
France.
</P>
<P>
Antonio Silva Aguiar, deputy director of the Macao Posts and
Telecommunications Department (CTT), announced Monday that CTT
will issue a set of four stamps to mark the sports event held
every four years.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1.8 million pieces will be issued for each
independent stamp, whose face value is at three patacas (about
0.375 U.S. dollars), 3.5 patacas, four patacas and 4.5 patacas
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Macao usually issues a set of commemorative stamps on major
sports events like the Olympics and the World Cup. These stamps
turn out to be very popular among local citizens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
