<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Chamber of Commerce Vows to Help Transition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A senior leader of the Macao Chamber
of Commerce (MCC), a prominent business group in Macao, said
Monday that his organization will play an active role in Macao's
smooth transition.
</P>
<P>
Ma Man Kei, MCC president, said at a reception marking the 85th
anniversary of the body Monday that the MCC will make great
efforts in all social affairs in the current time of difficulty.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1913, the MCC consisting of leading businessmen
is one of the most influential business bodies in Macao.
</P>
<P>
"We have, since its founding, striven for the protection of the
righteous interests of businessmen, for the social stability and
economic prosperity in Macao and for the development of friendship
between the Chinese people and Portuguese people," said Ma Man Kei
in his speech.
</P>
<P>
"In the time to come, we will continue to make efforts to that
end, and ...play an active role in all social affairs," he added.
</P>
<P>
Ma, also vice-chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said he is
confident of Macao's smooth transition and the realization of Deng
Xiaoping's idea of "one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
"We are convinced that under the care of the motherland, with
the joint efforts of all residents in Macao and with the joint
efforts from and sincere cooperation between China and Portugal,
it is certain that Macao will remain in good order and
economically prosperous," he said. "Deng Xiaoping's idea of 'one
country, two systems' will also be carried out in Macao
successfully."
</P>
<P>
The anniversary reception drew the attendance of Macao Governor
Vasco Rocha Vieira and Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch Director
Wang Qiren as well as some 500 celebrities in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira spoke highly of the role the MCC
has played over the past years, saying it has helped contribute to
Macao's development and modernization as well as the development
of the friendship between Portugal and China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
