<DOCNO> XIE19980608.0157 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> BIS Net Profit Reaches 259 M Gold Francs in 97/98 Financial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BASLE, SWITZERLAND, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The net profit of the Bank
for International Settelments (BIS) reached 259,160,599 gold francs
(one gold franc is about 1.94 U.S. dollars) in the financial year from
April 1, 1997 to March 31, 1998, compared to 194,289,449 gold francs
in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The above-mentioned figures are in the audited Banlace Sheet
approved at the 68th annual general meeting of the Basle-based BIS
here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Governor of the People's Bank of China Liu Mingkang was
among those present at the one-day meeting. The Chinese central bank
is one of the 45 central banks or official banking authorities which
possess the right of representation and of voting at BIS general
meetings.
</P>
<P>
According to the approved Balance Sheet, the assets of the BIS
totalled 62,450,174,630 gold francs up to March 31, 1998.
</P>
<P>
On the recommendation of the Board of Directors, the meeting
decided to distribute a dividend of 300 Swiss francs (one U.S. dollar
is about 1.47 Swiss francs) per share in respect of the fiancial year
ended on March 31, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The dividend will be payable on July 1, 1998 to shareholders whose
names are registered in the books of the bank on June 20, 1998. An
amount of 52,549,459 gold francs has been set aside out of the net
profit for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
The meeting also decided to transfer 41,322,228 gold francs to the
general reserve fund, 3,000,000 gold francs to the special dividend
reserve fund and 162,288,912 gold francs to the free reserve fund.
</P>
</TEXT>
