<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Fight Corruption, Bureaucracy: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 8 (Xinhua)-- Vietnam's Communist Party and
government are determined to fight against corruption and
bureaucracy, Prime Minister Phan Van Khai was quoted by the press
here Monday as saying.
</P>
<P>
The party and the government will "not tolerate or shield any
such acts, at any level or in any branch," Khai said in Ho Chi
Minh City.
</P>
<P>
The fight against corruption, smuggling and social evils is "a
complicated and long-term project," he said.
</P>
<P>
It needs close and effective coordination of all agencies,
services, branches and mass organizations, and the active support
and participation of the people, he said. 
</P>
