<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed broadly lower in thin trading Monday
due to uncertainty in the local currency -- ringgit.
</P>
<P>
The ringgit breached the 4.00 to one U.S. dollar level Monday
morning before bouncing back to 3.99 later in the day.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index lost 7.26
points to 497.79, the all-share Emas Index shed 2.09 points to
128.46, the Industrial Index fell 14.73 points to 988.44 and the
Second Board Index eased 0.36 of a point to 109.05.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers by 430 to 128 while 159 counters
were unchanged and 202 counters untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover stood at 99.174 million shares valued at
225.305 million ringgit (56.467 million U.S. dollars) from 106.737
million shares worth 278.997 million ringgit (69.924 million
dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the main board eased to 93.673 million shares
valued at 217.093 million ringgit (54.612 million dollars) from
99.647 million shares worth at 268.923 million ringgit (67.399
million dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover decreased to 5.501 million shares
valued at 8.212 million ringgit (2.058 million dollars) from last
Friday's 7.090 million shares worth at 10.074 million ringgit
(2.524 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market deals increased to 5.062 million shares valued at
9.736 million ringgit (2.44 million dollars) from 1.186 million
shares worth at 4.280 million ringgit (1.072 million dollars) last
Friday.
</P>
<P>
On sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 5.284
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products 6.732
million shares, construction 11.148 million shares,
trading/services 29.4 million shares, infrastructure 397,000
shares, finance 16.851 million shares, hotels 172,000 shares,
properties 9.717 million shares, plantation 2.723 million shares,
mining 178,200 shares, trusts 50,000 shares, closed/fund 45,000
shares and loans 10.973 million shares. 
