<HEADLINE> Another Substation Bombed in Western Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Another substation was bombed in
Kochchikade in Western province of Sri Lanka Monday morning,
according to police sources here .
</P>
<P>
The blowing up of substations in the country continues unabated
by a person, or possibly by a group, yet to be identified. With
this explosion, the number has risen to 12 this year, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred around 5:15 a.m. Monday. The sources
confirmed that the substation, 40 kilometers from Colombo, was a
complete wreck.
</P>
<P>
Destruction of substations had been taking place for over two
months now, and remains a mystery as no one has been arrested in
the connection, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The last incident was in Yakkala last week in the same
province. The authorities are planning to seek security for the
substations to prevent further damage, said the sources, adding
that measures are now being taken to construct security fences to
prevent easy access. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
