<HEADLINE> 2 Killed, 22 Injured as Train Falls Into River in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and 22
injured early Monday when a broad gauge train derailed and fell
into a shallow rivulet in the state of Assam, northeast India, the
Press Trust of India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
Sources from local railway headquarters said that seven coaches
of the passenger train slipped off the tracks while crossing a
railway bridge and fell into the rivulet in Kokrajhar district of
the state.
</P>
<P>
All of the injured, three of whom were reportedly in critical
condition, were admitted to local hospitals, PTI said.
</P>
<P>
Rail links between the northeast and the rest of the country
were suspended due to the accident, the cause of which could not
be immediately ascertained. 
</P>
