<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Economic Cooperation Strengthened in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Jiangxi Province has recently
signed 440 economic-cooperation contracts with Shanghai
Municipality and provinces like Zhejiang, Jiangsu and Fujian in
east China.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to trade-bidding activities in Shanghai held by a
delegation of 1,000 members from Jiangxi Province, these contracts
cover such areas as agriculture, industry, infrastructure
facilities and the service industry, and involve investments
exceeding 5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Besides Jiangxi, other provinces in east China like Jiangsu,
Anhui, and Fujian have also held trade-bidding activities in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Comments from the "People's Daily (East China Page)" pointed
out that economic cooperation among east China's provinces had
unpredictable significance.
</P>
<P>
Shu Shengyou, governor of Jiangxi Province, said that it is
necessary to strengthen regional mutual assistance among east
China's provinces.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that during 1996-1997, Jiangxi Province signed
146 contracts involving 1.24 billion yuan with Shanghai. During
the 1991-1995 period, Jiangxi and Shanghai signed 160 contracts
involving 250 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Kowloon railway and exploration of the Yangtze
River provided an opportunity for Jiangxi, which has geographical
advantages with neighboring Fujian and Guangdong provinces and
convenient communication with Beijing and Kowloon.
</P>
<P>
Shu said Jiangxi was short of construction funding, and that
the province will give preferential policies and improve the
investment environment to attract more investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
