<HEADLINE> Balkan Meeting Expected to Help Solve Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISTANBUL, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Turkey said that it hopes the
Balkan foreign minister's meeting starting here Monday will
contribute to solving the Kosovo problem.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Foreign Ministry spokesman Necati Utkan told reporters
that the two-day meeting will center on the worsening situation in
the Yugoslav province.
</P>
<P>
"I'm sure that this issue will take a place on the agenda and
will also be one of the important issues that they (the foreign
ministers) will discuss," Utkan said.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of Albania, Bulgaria, Greece, Macedonia,
Romania, Turkey and the Yugoslav Federation will discuss regional
security and economic cooperation at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Croatia and Bosnia are participating in the meeting as
observers.
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo issue has been worsening since February when bloody
clashes erupted between Serbian police and ethnic Albanians who
demand independence from the Yugoslav Federation.
</P>
<P>
Heavy casualties have been reported in the Yugoslav province
and caused grave concern in the international community and the
Balkans as well. 
</P>
</TEXT>
