<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Congratulates OAU Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji sent a
message of congratulations Monday to the 34th Assembly of the
Heads of State and Government of the Organization of African Unity
(OAU).
</P>
<P>
"On the occasion of the convocation of the 34th Assembly of the
Heads of State and Government of the Organization of African Unity
and the warm celebration by the African people of the 35th
anniversary of the founding of the Organization of African Unity,
I wish to extend, on behalf of the Chinese Government and people,
our warm congratulations to the Assembly," Zhu said in the
message.
</P>
<P>
"Over the past 35 years, the OAU, holding high the banner of
African solidarity, has fulfilled victoriously the great historic
mission of national independence and decolonization of the
continent through its unremitting efforts."
</P>
<P>
"We are glad to see that over recent years the OAU has made
gratifying achievements in its active efforts to maintain regional
peace and stability and promote the continent's economic recovery
and development," Zhu added.
</P>
<P>
While the world is moving toward multi-polarity in present
days, "the political situation in Africa is becoming stabilized,
its economy improving, and its regional cooperation picking up
speed," the Chinese premier said.
</P>
<P>
"The international community should pay more attention to
Africa's development and support the efforts of the African
nations to rejuvenate their economies and explore ways of
development suited to their specific national conditions," Zhu
said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese and African peoples enjoy a long traditional
friendship with each other, Zhu said. "China will, as always, join
hands with African countries, to work for common economic
development and a more splendid world," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
