<HEADLINE> Key Projects Operational In East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A number of key infrastructure
projects in east China's Fujian province have gone into operation,
government sources said.
</P>
<P>
Provincial economic planners say that the southeast coastal
province is to put a total of 110 billion yuan into infrastructure
projects this year.
</P>
<P>
A polypropylene project at the Fujian Oil Refinery Corp. was
put into production at the end of May, able to produce 70,000 tons
of polypropylene a year, marking the end that Fujian did not have
any large petrochemical project.
</P>
<P>
Designed by China itself, the project costs a total of 650
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The company now has an annual oil refining capacity of four
million tons and is expected to have an annual oil refining
capacity of 12 million tons when a second-phase project of the
company is completed. And at the same time, a project is planned
to produce 600,000 tons of polyethylene a year.
</P>
<P>
With the completion of the two projects, Fujian will become one
of the country's major petro-chemical industrial bases, the
provincial government said.
</P>
<P>
To meet the demand for electronic information, the province
recently began work on a wide-band multimedia network for nine
prefectures and cities and various industrial sectors.
</P>
<P>
Full-swing construction has begun on a power plant, an
expressway and several other key projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
