<HEADLINE> 400-year-old Human Body Found in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A 400-year-old body of a male human
was found recently in east China's Jiangxi Province, according to
today's Beijing Youth Daily.
</P>
<P>
Some road workers in Xingzi County discovered a 3.5-meter-long,
2-meter-wide, 2.5-meter-deep tomb, in which there were three
coffins.
</P>
<P>
They opened the larger one in the middle and found it filled
with clear water, in which there lay a 1.9-meter-tall male body
intact.
</P>
<P>
According to the inscription on the memorial tablet, the tomb
was for a man named Qian who was an official of the Ming dynasty
(1368-1644). He died 476 years ago, in his sixties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
