<HEADLINE> World Bank Funds Kampala Drainage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has announced a 12
million U.S. Dollars donation for the reconstruction of Nakivubo
Channel, a key drainage project in Kampala.
</P>
<P>
The donation to be released soon is part of the bank's
continued support to the city council's development program aimed
at improving delivery of services in the capital.
</P>
<P>
The World Bank team leader, Gautam Sengupta, told a press
conference here over the weekend that the project, expected to
begin March 1999, mainly covers widening and deepening of the
channel as well as putting more crossing points on it.
</P>
<P>
He said there is need to have human, technical and financial
resources to effectively improve service delivery in the city.
</P>
<P>
On the same occasion, World Bank Resident Representative
Randolph Harris warned against mismanagement of the fund, saying
that in some cases the money could not reach the beneficiaries
due to inefficiency in financial management. 
</P>
