<HEADLINE> Chinese River Dikes Operational Before Flood Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A new dike along the Huaihe, one of
the major rivers flowing across China's Anhui Province, went
operational recently, changing the river's flood flowing capacity
from 4,500 cubic meters per second to 6,600 cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
The dike is located near Hefei, Anhui's capital, and was built
in connection with the West Lake Water Storage Zone, which has a
capacity of 3 billion cubic meters of water. As many as 18,000
people had been relocated for the project, and a 12.4-kilometer
dike added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
