<DOCNO> XIE19980608.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Remote Sensing Technology Helping China Predict Earthquakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, June 8 (Xinhua) -- China has got its short-term
earthquake prediction up to 50 percent thanks to help from
satellite infrared remote-sensing technology.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese predicted 15 earthquakes last year, with an
accuracy rate above 50 percent, in time, location, and magnitude,
according to China Aerospace Corporation's Satellite Prediction
Research Center for Natural Disasters.
</P>
<P>
Predicting earthquakes is thought to be impossible by many
scientists, but Chinese scientists believe that the satellite
technology, when combined with other technology, can bring new
accuracy to earthquake prediction.
</P>
<P>
The biggest problem with thermal infrared technology now is
that clouds can interfere with the satellite detection, explains
Qiang Zuji of the prediction center, but this problem can be
overcome by the use of microwave technology and China is designing
a system of small satellites for just this purpose.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980608.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gansu Sees Increasing Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
had signed 595 economic and technology cooperation agreements,
worth 4.1 billion yuan and 8.68 million US dollars in overseas
investment by the end of 1997.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official says that Gansu did this to
create better economic conditions and that the cooperation
involves large investment in resource exploration, infrastructure,
high-tech industry, and township-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The projects are meant to help areas with little economic
base. One of these, the Longnan Mountain area, signed three
contracts with Shenzhen and Hong Kong for a hydro-electric power
station, an apple orchard, and Chinese medicine processing
project, involving 829 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Economic cooperation organizations are also working to get
local products on the market. Last October, at the 9th West China
Trade Fair, delegations from Pingliang, Tianshui, and Longnan in
Gansu did over 600 million yuan worth of business.  
</P>
