</P>
<P>
-- The size and timing of the third pullback emerged Sunday as
the last major obstacle to an agreement among Israel, the United
States and the Palestinian National Authority. Palestinian
insistence on receiving more than the 2 percent believed to have
been offered by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu dampened hopes
of an early breakthrough.
</P>
<P>
Haaretz:
</P>
<P>
-- An argument broke out at Israels weekly cabinet meeting
Sunday over a proposal to allow Arabs to volunteer for national
service. National Infrastructure Minister Ariel Sharon, Minister
of Agriculture and Environment Rafael Eitan and Science Minister
Michael Etan were said to oppose the proposal, stating that
opening the national service for Arabs would endanger Israel's
security.
</P>
<P>
