<HEADLINE> Planting Trees As A Birthday Celebration In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Xu Xiaoping, who lives in
Nanchang, the capital of east China's Jiangxi Province, planted a
China fir near the Jingjiu (Beijing-Kowloon) Railway line for his
tenth birthday this year and says he thinks it will grow as fast
and healthy as he does, and will see who is taller by the time he
finishes middle school.
</P>
<P>
Many of the children at Xu's school have decided to celebrate
their birthdays in the same way, and Xu says that this is quite
significant.
</P>
<P>
A local education department official says that they have had
this program since 1995, and that the response by local students
and their parents has been good.
</P>
<P>
The province's students have planted 1.45 million trees, 80
percent of which are along the Jingjiu Railway line, which
connects Beijing and Kowloon in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
A third of the 2,000-kilometer railway line is in Jiangxi. The
Chinese Government plans to turn the railway line into a "green
corridor", and Xu says, "We should make the railway more
beautiful."  
</P>
