<HEADLINE> China's Largest Water Diversion Cofferdam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A concrete cofferdam in southwest
China's Yunnan Province is China's largest, at 183.5 meters long,
6.3 meters wide, and 53 meters high.
</P>
<P>
It is part of the controls to hold back water or divert floods
during construction of the Dachao Mountain Hydro-electric Power
Station, which is to be completed in 2003, local engineers say.
</P>
<P>
It lies between a temporary earth-stone cofferdam on the upper
reaches and the concrete dam of the power station, which is
planned for 1.35 million kw annual capacity, and will cost nearly
9 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
