<HEADLINE> Central Chinese Farmers Buy Plane For Sightseeing Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A crowd of farmers gathered on the
banks of a reservoir in the city of Zaoyang in China's Hubei
Province recently to witness the maiden flight of a sightseeing
plane that twelve of their fellow villagers bought.
</P>
<P>
This bold move came from Liu Changbi, after several visits to
tourist sites at the nearby town of Xiongji.
</P>
<P>
So, he got together with eleven of the villagers, raised more
than 300,000 yuan, and bought a seaplane from an institute
belonging to the China Aerospace Corp.
</P>
<P>
The village used to be a poor mountainous place but that is now
changing as farmers there began to shift their gaze to tourism.
</P>
