<HEADLINE> Flood Protection Work In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Anhui Province in east China is
raising more than a billion yuan (about 120 million US dollars)
annually in various ways for facilities to fight floods, according
to the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
This agricultural province on the lower reaches of the Yangtze
River has been plagued by floods since the 1990s. As much as 1.75
billion yuan has been raised for 6 water resource projects in the
Huaihe River Valley and about 200 million cubic meters of soil and
stone moved.
</P>
<P>
In the Yangtze River Valley, flood control facilities on the
Wuwei, Tongma, Yuxihe, and Wuhu have been built or improved and 60
percent of the 3 billion yuan in financing for agricultural
development has been allocated for water facilities.
</P>
<P>
The province has a new way to raise money. The provincial
capital city of Hefei plans to raise 100 million yuan for water
projects during the Ninth Five-year Plan period (1996-2000) and
the local government has put 5 million yuan into the Chuhe River
treatment project, for which local people raised 22.5 million yuan
themselves.  
</P>
</TEXT>
