<DOCNO> XIE19980608.0228 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Needs to Rely on Consumers Credit to Boost Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- While commodities are in
oversupply, many Chinese consumers are lacking money to buy what
they want to buy.
</P>
<P>
In view of the Chinese economists, the way to solve this
dilemma is to develop consumers' credit, which is seriously
lacking in the country.
</P>
<P>
The achievement of China's eight percent growth of Gross
Domestic Products(GDP) this year will largely depend on the
thriving of the consumers' market, the economists argue.
</P>
<P>
After years of economic boom, China is now at a stage of
consumption structure escalation, featuring more urban people
planning to buy cars and homes and more farmers in need of
electrical appliances.
</P>
<P>
However, while more credit loans are injected into the
production sector, the consumption credit is still considered
backward in China.
</P>
<P>
As a result, when ordinary wage-earners want to buy some
money-consuming items, they find it difficult to afford it all at
once, and have to save money for sometime before buying.
</P>
<P>
The economists thus suggested efforts be made to accelerate the
introduction of buyer's credit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980608.0229 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Regulations on Safety of Drifting Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese and foreign river drifters
will find their safety better guaranteed in China as regulations
on river drifting safety has come out.
</P>
<P>
Divided into 29 articles, the "Interim Methods Governing the
Safety of River Drifting Tourism" covers qualification of
operators, the examination standards on safety facilities,
personnel training, hydrological monitoring, and the dredging of
rivers.
</P>
<P>
According to incomplete statistics, over one million Chinese
and foreign adventurers take part in river drifting in China a
year. There are 55 operators across the country offering such
program.
</P>
<P>
"We should constantly improve the safety facilities and
management for river drifting in China," said Cui Yanan, an
official with the China National Tourism Administration, the
promulgator of the new regulations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
