<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wellington, June 8 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market's
main index shed 1.5 percent in heavy trading Monday as short-term
interest rates took off on the back of a sharply weaker New
Zealand dollar.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 31 points lower at 2,104 with a turnover
 of 140 million dollars (71 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Fltecher Forest was the only main leader to gain, up 2 cents to
102 cents.
</P>
<P>
Among the weaker leaders, Air New Zealand, Brierley Investment
and Carter Holt Harvey eased 3 cents each to 187 cents, 89 cents
and 207 cents separately. Fletcher Energy and Lion Nathan lost 10
cents each to 532 cents and 435 cents respectively. Telecom
dipped 4 cents to 842 cents. And Fletcher Building dived 12 cents
to 297 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, falls outnumbered rises by 82 to 16. 
