WASHINGTON -- The military of the United States used nerve gas
to kill defectors during the Vietnam war, U.S. media said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Adm. Thomas Moorer, former chairman of the Joint Chiefs of
Staff was quoted as saying that sarin nerve gas was used in 1970
in a secret raid into Laos, according to a joint report of Cable
News Networks (CNN) and Time magazine. Other military officials
who participated in the operation said their job was to kill
defectors from the U.S. troops. (U.S.-Vietnam War-Nerve Gas)
</P>
