<HEADLINE> Italy Welcomes Stopping of Air Raid Between Ethiopia, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The stopping of mutual air raid
between Ethiopia and Eritrea is a good sign for Italy which is
closely following the deteriorating situation there, said Italian
Prime Minister Romano Prodi Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In Italian central city Bologna, Prodi told ANSA news agency
that Italy is in contact with the warring neighbors and diplomatic
mediation is ongoing.
</P>
<P>
Italy, the colonial master of both countries between 1936 and
1941, has evacuated by air 237 Italians and 114 nationals of other
countries from Eritrean capital Asmara's airport by Sunday
morning, said ANSA.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of foreigners were fleeing Eritrea by air on Saturday
nights after Ethiopia agreed to suspend air strikes until 07:00
a.m.(0400 GMT) on Sunday in the worsening conflict between the
Horn of Africa neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian war planes have hit Asmara airport three times since
violence over a border dispute erupted Friday, and Eritrean planes
attacked the northern Ethiopian provincial capital of Makalle,
leaving dozens of people dead and over hundred injured.  
</P>
