<HEADLINE> Human Trafficking Gang Cracked in Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Czech police cracked down an
international gang engaged in human trafficking and captured all
the 19 suspects, spokesman of the Czech Police Bureau Ivana
Moosova said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Moosova said that crack down took place on Sunday morning by
the Czech anti-organized crime force, mobile force and frontier
force jointly.
</P>
<P>
This was the biggest crime organization on human traffic the
Czech police had cracked down.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, the gang had peddled nearly 3,000 people to western
countries fetching 10,000--30,000 U.S. dollars apiece.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said human trafficking activities had run rampant
in recent years, and the Czech police would spare no efforts in
the combat against such crime. 
