<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Increase Rubber Block Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BANGKOK, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Thailand plans to increase rubber
block export over the next five years to meet rising demand from
the United States and Europe, the Bangkok Post reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Chakarn Saengruksawong, director of the
Rubber Research Institute, as saying that the export growth target
will rise from 600,000 tons per year, or 20 percent of the present
production, to 30 percent over the next five years.
</P>
<P>
The United States is currently Thailand's main overseas market
for rubber block, Chakarn said.
</P>
<P>
Thai rubber block captured 32 percent of the U.S. market in
1997 as competition from Malaysia and Indonesia declined due to
lower production and exports, the director said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is expected to export 1.9 million tons of natural
rubber this year while Malaysia and Indonesia are expected to
export one million and 1.6 million tons respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980608.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-06-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's BOI Signs 114 Ventures Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Board of Investment
(BOI) signed a total of 114 agreements on project with local or
foreign ventures from November 1997 to May 1998, according to the
BOI sources Monday.
</P>
<P>
Under these agreements, investments of 3.311 billion U.S.
dollars would be brought in the country and a total of 21,676
persons would be employed.
</P>
<P>
The projects include 52 local ventures and 62 ventures from
countries and regions like the United States, Germany, Taiwan and
Hong Kong, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The projects are diversified into a wide range of areas such as
cultivation and export of pineapples, manufacture and export of
non-quota garments; mining and processing of granite blocks for
export and computer software.
</P>
<P>
Other areas include cultivation of sugar cane, manufacture of
machines and tools and the establishment of a radio broadcasting
network, the sources added. 
