<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peasant Risks His Life to Save Panda in Southwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A sick and hungry panda was
recently saved from drowning in China's Sichuan Province, thanks
to a group of farmers.
</P>
<P>
The panda was moving along the waters of a turbulent river when
the peasants saw her. To keep the panda from falling in the river,
one of them, Yang Yanfang, ran up and grabbed the panda. The two
rolled down the slope before Yang caught a tree branch, just a few
meters above the rushing waters.
</P>
<P>
Other peasants immediately came down and grabbed the panda and
Yang, whose arms were bleeding as a result of the tussle with the
panda.
</P>
<P>
The animal was sent to the county forestry bureau for medical
treatment and after it recovered, was returned to the Labahe
Nature Reserve.
</P>
<P>
This was the second lucky panda to be saved by peasants this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
