<HEADLINE> Bulls Routs Jazz 96-54 in NBA Finals Game 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Michael Jordan scored 24
points and Toni Kukoc added 16 on Sunday as the Chicago Bulls
routed the Utah Jazz 96-54 in Game 3 of the NBA Finals, holding
the Jazz to the fewest points in NBA history.
</P>
<P>
The Bulls, who lead the best-of-seven series 2-1, will enjoy
two more home-court advantaged games, with Game 4 arranged on
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
It is the biggest margin for a team ever has won in the NBA
Finals history. With this heavy blow, the Jazz looked completely
smashed in confidence and seemed unable to match the Bulls at the
United Center where the Bulls have a record of 35 wins against
four losses.
</P>
<P>
"Everybody had a good time out there," Jordan said. "We came
out and played hard. We put the effort and intensity in and as a
result we could relax a little in the fourth quarter."
</P>
<P>
Utah's 54 points broke the NBA record of 55 set earlier this
season by the Indian Pacers and was 17 fewer than the Finals
record of 71 by Syracuse in 1955.
</P>
<P>
"I'm somewhat embarrassed for NBA basketball, for our guys
to come out and have no fight at all," Utah coach Jerry Sloan
said. "They got all the loose balls and all the rebounds."
</P>
<P>
Karl Malone, who had a shooting 14-for-41 over the previous two
games, entered the game like a diffrent man, shot in all his first
four jumpers plus a pair of driving to basket along with his 22
points.
</P>
<P>
But the rest of the team only contributed 13-for-59 shooting,
with Howard Eisley 0-6, Bryon Russell and Greg Ostertag 1-for-7
each.
</P>
<P>
the Jazz made frequent pass errors and had 26 turnovers in the
games. Malone and John Stockton combined to make 12 turnovers to
hand in Chicago 22 points. The first half ended at 49-31 in favor
of the Bulls.
</P>
<P>
The second half was an entire lopsided affair with the Bulls
ran away quickly to increase the lead by 23 points five minutes
into the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
In the final eight minutes, with the first line-up of the both
sides rested on bench, the Bulls reserves humiliated their
counterparts with 30-5 run to wind up the game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
