<HEADLINE> China's Metal Output up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 8 (Xinhua) -- China turned out 9.81 million tons
of pig iron in March, up 6.9 percent over the same period of
1997, according to the latest figures from the State Statistics
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The steel output amounted to 9.59 million tons, up 5.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of ferro alloy reached 262,600 tons, up 0.3
percent. 
</P>
