<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany's Schumacher Wins Canadian Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Germany's racer Michael Schumacher
won the Player's Grand Prix of Canada in Montreal Sunday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Ferrari driver became a three-time Canadian Grand Prix
winner, who took the checkered flag at Circuit Gilles Villeneuve
in one hour 40:57.355 seconds.
</P>
<P>
It was the 29th victory of Schumacher's career and his second
of the season. The race was broadcast live by the Canadian
Broadcasting Corporation Television.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Giancarlo Fisichella of Benetton, and Schumacher's
teammate Britain's Eddie Irvine was ranked second and third
respectively.
</P>
<P>
During the 69-lap race, Schumacher didn't cruise ahead all
along. At one time, he fell behind Fisichella when he was handed
a 10-second stop-go penalty for pushing German Heinz-Harald
Frentzen off the track.
</P>
<P>
Yet, he regained the lead again on lap 42 when Fisichella
stopped for fuel. He finished 16.662 seconds ahead of the Italian
driver.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's race in Montreal was the seventh of 16 races in Grand
Prix events in the Formula One World Driving Championship.
</P>
</TEXT>
