<HEADLINE> 45TH International Rally Acropolis Begins in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 7 (Xinhhua) -- The 45th International Rally
Acropolis began here Sunday with the participation of 103 cars.
</P>
<P>
The participating cars will cover an overall distance of
1031.97 kilometers over three days, which will include 17 special
sections totaling 388.76 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's race, which began at the foot of Athens' most famous
landmark -- the "sacred rock," ended at Delphi.
</P>
<P>
After two-times world champion Tomi Makinnen of Finland was
forced out of the rally due to mechanical problems of his
Mitsubishi Lancer, Belgium's driver Bruno Thiry, who had led from
the start, also retired on the fifth stage at
Evangelistria. Britain's Richard Burns, in a Mitsubishi, took the
lead with a 4.5 seconds advantage over compatriot Colin Mcray and
two stages remaining.
</P>
<P>
Competitors will on Monday set out from and return to Delphi
after covering a total distance of 336.76 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The third and last stage of the rally will on Tuesday be run
from Delphi and back again, covering a distance of 328,73
kilometers. 
</P>
