<HEADLINE> Australia Takes Bronze Medal at Basketball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Australia rallied from a 12-piont
halftime deficit to beat defending champion Brazil 72-67 Sunday,
taking the brozne medal of the Women's World Basketball
Championship.
</P>
<P>
The Australians, who placed third four years ago, traild in the
first half 33-45, used a 15-3 run to equaled the game 48-48 on
Michelle Griffiths's basket 5:15 into the second half.
</P>
<P>
Then after the score tied several times Australia took the lead
61-60 on Annie La Fleur's three-pointer with 5:20 to play and kept
the edge to the buzz.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time for the Australian women's team to take a
medal in the history of the world championships.
</P>
<P>
Forward Carla Porter scored 26 points to lead Australia and
Michele Timms added 11.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's center Alessandrac De Olivira was the team's top
scorer with 21 points and she also grabbed 10 rebounds. Guard
Cristina Luz Helen scored 18 including two three-pointers.
</P>
<P>
Australia lost to Russia 76-82 in Saturday's semi-finals while
Brazil, who beat China to win the gold medal at last championship,
was defeated by the United States in another semi-final.
</P>
<P>
The Americans and Russians will compete for the gold medal
later Sunday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
