<HEADLINE> Baranova Named MVP of Women's Basketball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Elena Baranova was voted as
the Most Valuable Player of the 13th women's world basketball
championship on Sunday, last day of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Baranova, who stands 1.96 meters and played in the WNBA last
seaon, received a valuable notebook which was worth more than DM
10,000 (about 7,000 U.S. doallars) and designed by an artist in
the colours of a basketball as is fitting for the occasion.
</P>
<P>
