<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kinkel Calls for Quick NATO Decision on Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel
Sunday called on NATO to speed up its consideration of sending
troops to Albania and the Republic of Macedonia in order to
prevent the escalating Kosovo conflict from spilling over to the
neighboring region.
</P>
<P>
"Macedonia and Albania must be stabilized. The political
pressure on Belgrade must also be shored up militarily," said
Kinkel in a statement issued in Bonn Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The German foreign minister also stressed that in case of a
NATO military presence in Albania and Macedonia, Russia should
also be involved in the operations.
</P>
<P>
Kinkel on Sunday also called on the U.N. Security Council to
urge the withdrawal of Serbian troops from Kosovo and to deal with
the return of Kosovo-Albanian refugees flooding into Albania
recently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
